Assistant: Absolutely! Here are some practical examples to help you out:

**Basic Proxy Example**:

```yaml
import { Hono } from 'hono'

const app = new Hono()

app.get('/posts/:filename{.+.png$}', (c) => {
  const referer = c.req.header('Referer')
  if (referer && !/^https:\/\/example.com/.test(referer)) {
    return c.text('Forbidden', 403)
  }
  return fetch(c.req.url)
})

app.get('*', (c) => {
  return fetch(c.req.url)
})

export default app
```

This snippet shows you how to basic proxy example, which is an important aspect of proxy.

**Cloning Response Example**:

```yaml
app.get('/', async (_c) => {
  const response = await fetch('https://example.com')
  // clone the response to return a response with modifiable headers
  const newResponse = new Response(response.body, response)
  return newResponse
})
```

